summary: I think Tony's retirement is gonna be him tracing all the good superheroes out there and making them brand new, personalized...
body: I think Tony’s retirement is gonna be him tracing all the good superheroes out there and making them brand new, personalized suits, so he’s gonna retire from the fights but he’s gonna make sure the people that fight do it safely, and this is what I want to see in the final post credit scene: various superheros coming home to find a parcel waiting for them, all signed “TS”, like he did with Peter, or even with Harley in a way, and maybe we’ll even get to see some of the Marvel Netflix superheroes or AOS or the next superheroes Marvel is gonna introduce in the future. It’d be a nice way to gather everyone that belongs in the MCU and that we didn’t get to see on the big screen.

title: lay me down (tell me i've been found)
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2BuQVsV

by coffeeinallcaps

The collar is a little on the heavy side, and incredibly soft against Bucky’s skin. Even softer than he thought it would be. It seems to fit snugly, and for a second he feels like he can’t breathe. Then, Steve slides two fingers under the collar and runs them along the inside, almost all the way around. Bucky shivers. Goose bumps spread down his back, his arms.
“How does it feel?” Steve murmurs, hooking his fingers into the ring and giving a gentle tug on it.
Bucky swallows. Nods.

(In which billionaire businessman Steve shows up and turns Bucky’s life into an improbable fantasy.)

“How does it feel?” Steve murmurs, hooking his fingers into the ring and giving a gentle tug on it.
Bucky swallows. Nods.

summary: every time tony was hopeful about something in the mcu they made it extra sure that his hopes are crushed like 20 mins...
body:
every time tony was hopeful about something in the mcu they made it extra sure that his hopes are crushed like 20 mins later

like ooh look at that new peaceful direction your company is taking, surely your only father figure wouldnt mind and try to kill you with your own inventions over it.

oh look you made an invention to keep your heart in one piece and the shrapnels in your chest at bay, surely it wouldnt start poisoning your body right when you need it to work most!

oh look you built a whole army of robots to protect you and pepper, too bad it was too slow to spare her the same fucking nightmares you kept having after the arc reactor almost ended up killing you!

oh look the government agency you funded called you a incompatible human and honestly only wants you for the things you created even though without you they wouldnt exist!

oh look you tried to save the world by building ultron and have it defend everyone from the threats from outer space, and it ended up almost wiping humanity from the face of the earth instead.

oh look the team you invested your time and efforts in used the same gear you built for them - against you!

oh look your only actual friend from said group, you know, the one who you paid attention to the most and made sure he feels safe and comfortable around the same people that used to want him dead, fell asleep the moment you started telling him about your own issues! and you thought he fucking cared!

oh look you made the biggest leap in science yet to make a perfect suit to protect you and your future kid you just now felt safe having with your wife to be, too bad that it couldnt protect the kid you already kind of have and you had to watch him die in your arms instead, helpless and knowing your best wasnt nearly enough to spare everyone else the pain youve been feeling as long as you remember.

oh look, youre alone on a fucking planet, ages away from earth, you dont know who died and who remained, you dont want to fucking know anything besides how to fix this spaceship and go back home, all you do know is that you failed everyone again, and that youre tired, God. so fucking tired.
